  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will develop and pilot a training programme that benefits refugees, asylum seekers and vulnerable migrant workers, with a strong focus on engaging with women. Participants will gain skills, knowledge and experience to support them as they move towards paid employment or self -employment. In the longer term the programme will also promote opportunities and provide support for women&apos;s enterprise, in catering and related areas of work. It will develop and create a flexible modular accredited training programme built around food preparation, catering, food hygiene, and additional modules that support participants&apos; development.</narrative>
  </description>
